    <briefdescription>
<para>Shifts the elements of a fixed-point vector by a specified number of bits. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>There are separate functions for Q7, Q15, and Q31 data types. The underlying algorithm used is: <preformatted>
    dst[n] = src[n] &lt;&lt; shift,   0 &lt;= n &lt; block_size.
</preformatted> If <computeroutput>shift</computeroutput> is positive then the elements of the vector are shifted to the left. If <computeroutput>shift</computeroutput> is negative then the elements of the vector are shifted to the right.</para>
<para>The functions support in-place computation allowing the source and destination pointers to reference the same memory buffer. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
